<Author>dantescraps2007
<Content>Practicality and Location! Again, TripAdvisor steered us correctly. My husband and I were looking for a practical little hotel in a great location that wasn't going to break the bank while we visited Paris from Christmas to New Year's. If you are a looking for a cozy little place that's close to everything, this is it. The room was smaller but this is the kind of hotel you're using as a home base, so it was great. It was clean, safe, and warm during the cold spell that descended on Paris that week so who could ask for more? The staff were very helpful at all times, day or night. There is always someone on premise, which is excellent. I will say the walls are a bit on the thin side but it's nothing unmanageable. We did not partake of the breakfast here as there were so many great little bakeries and cafes near by but the menu listed many old standbys, which would be great if you're a cautious eater or have kids. The hotel is very close to the Metro (which is very safe, clean, and easy to use) so it's very handy. It's also only a 5 minute walk from Rue Mouffetard (many little restaurants and bars- I highly recommend Le Jardin d'Ivy), 5 minutes from a little daily market down the street, and 10 minutes from Notre Dame. So, if you're looking for a homey little place where you can put your feet up at the end of a long day of sight-seeing, walking, or eating (as was the case with us), this is a great little bargain! 
