<Content>Perfect Little Hotel! We just spent 9 days at Hotel Saint-Christophe, and loved every minute of it. With the semaine rate, it came to about 100 euros per night (including a decent-sized breakfast) -- a great deal! It was super-clean, very quiet, and only a block from everything you might need. Place de la Contrascarpe was a block away, Place Monge (street market) and rue Mouffetard (a bazillion restaurants, street market, etc.) were each a block away, tons of little neighborhood cafes and bistros, a laundramat and small supermarket each a block away, two Metro stops and numerous buses nearby, and the Arene de Lutece half a block away. We could walk to Notre Dame, Luxembourg Gardens, the Pantheon, St. Michel, St. Germain. There's a computer near the lobby, and you can purchase units of time to check your e-mail or keep in touch with folks back home.The staff couldn't have been nicer or more helpful -- we never left or arrived without having a pleasant conversation with someone. One morning, I heard a noise outside the window and opened it discover there were workers painting the building. (We'd been told they'd be there, but I'd forgotten.) When I closed the window, I discovered I'd gotten white paint all over my brand-new black jacket ... and the staff sprang into action. They came up with turpentine to remove the paint, then scrubbed it with something else to make it smell better. (The smell wore off in half an hour anyway.) Even though it was completely my fault, they were so nice about it. I'd recommend this hotel to anyone who wants to stay in a real (not tourist-y) Parisian neighborhood -- and I'll definitely stay there again. 
